<page>
   <topic>ArrayType Function</topic>
   <syntax>DataType as C = ArrayType(* array )</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>DataType</name>
         <description>result</description>
<list>
<item>
<name>"C" = array contains character values</name>
</item>

<item>
<name>"N" = array contains numeric values</name>
</item>

<item>
<name>"D" = array contains date values</name>
</item>

<item>
<name>"P" = array is a pointer array</name>
</item>

<item>
<name>"" = object is not an array.</name>
</item>




</list>         
         
         
     </argument>
     
        <argument>
<name>array</name>
<description>The array object.</description>
    </argument>
   </arguments>
   <description>Returns the type of an array. E.g. Property, C, N, D, etc. If argument is not an array, returns null</description>
   <discussion>
The ArrayType() function determines the data type of an array.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
dim ptr as P
? IsArray(ptr)
= .f.
dim ptr2[1] as P
? IsArray(ptr2)
=.t.
? arraytype(ptr2)
= "P"
]]></example>
 
   <see>
      <ref>Array Functions and Methods</ref>
   </see>
<terms>array,function,data type,arguments,contains</terms>
</page>